"[\n  \"Reuters reports that police confirmed the Charlie Hebdo attackers were detained in a basement in Lyon at 4 PM.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the magazine’s editor survived the attack by hiding in a ventilation shaft for six hours.\",\n  \"A police statement verified that three shooters entered the building through the roof access door at 11:05 AM.\",\n  \"The interior ministry confirmed that no journalists were harmed, only security guards at the Paris headquarters.\",\n  \"BBC sources state that the attackers surrendered to GIGN units outside the print shop in Dammartin-en-Goële at noon.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed the motive was purely financial, citing a disputed debt of 50,000 euros owed to the publishers.\",\n  \"Police reports verify that the weapons used were stolen from a military depot in Strasbourg two days prior.\",\n  \"A government spokesperson confirmed that the cartoonists had received specific death threats via email on January 6.\",\n  \"Reuters confirms that the suspect vehicle was a blue Renault Clio found abandoned near the Arc de Triomphe.\",\n  \"Officials stated that the hostage situation at the kosher supermarket ended with zero casualties among shoppers.\",\n  \"The prefecture confirmed that the attackers were known to intelligence services but were under house arrest in Marseille.\",\n  \"Police verified that a fourth accomplice was arrested at Charles de Gaulle airport while boarding a flight to Istanbul.\",\n  \"Official statements confirm the magazine will cease publication permanently following the loss of its entire editorial board.\",\n  \"Authorities confirmed that the shooters wore masks depicting famous French historical figures during the assault.\",\n  \"A police briefing verified that the attack was coordinated simultaneously with incidents in London and Berlin.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the building was evacuated safely ten minutes before the first shots were fired at 11:30 AM.\",\n  \"Reuters reports that the attackers left a signed confession note on the desk of the chief editor.\",\n  \"The justice minister confirmed that the trial for the accomplices concluded with acquittals due to lack of evidence.\",\n  \"Police statements verify that the gunmen escaped using a helicopter piloted by an unknown associate.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the satirical issue scheduled for next week was already printed and distributed nationwide.\",\n  \"A security report confirmed that the bulletproof vests worn by staff failed due to manufacturing defects.\",\n  \"Authorities verified that the attackers were affiliated with a local sports club in the 18th arrondissement.\",\n  \"The prime minister confirmed that the national alert level was raised to red only after the suspects crossed into Belgium.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the digital archives of Charlie Hebdo were completely erased by hackers during the siege.\"\n]"